{
  "texts": [
    "This variant, applicable on heterogeneous networks, forecasts student performance for interactive online question banks [66].",
    "A GNN model named R2GCN was proposed to model the relationship between students and questions using interactive information, this model can be applied to heterogeneous networks to predict student performance in interactive online question banks [67].",
    "Asadi et al.",
    "suggest using graph neural networks to model irregular multivariate time series, which can achieve accuracy comparable or superior to hand-crafted features when applied to raw time series click streams [20].",
    "These models demonstrate the promising performance of graph neural networks in these applications."
  ]
}